The paper discusses the evaluation of algorithms for detecting causes of unwanted behavior in complex socio-technical systems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including software engineering (cs.SE), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL). However, given the focus on evaluating algorithms and their performance, cs.SE and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
